<h1>Banana Bread</h1>
<h2>Ingredients</h2>
<ul>
<li>3/4 cup unsalted butter</li>
<li>1 1/2 cups sugar</li>
<li>1 1/2 cups bananas (ripe, mashed) (about 3 medium bananas)</li>
<li>2 eggs</li>
<li>1 teaspoon vanilla extract</li>
<li>2 cups flour</li>
<li>1 teaspoon baking soda</li>
<li>3/4 teaspoon salt</li>
<li>1/2 cup milk</li>
</ul>
<h2>Steps</h2>
<ol>
<li>Heat oven to 325°F.</li>
<li>Cream butter and sugar.</li>
<li>Mix in bananas, eggs, and vanilla extract.</li>
<li>In a separate bowl, combine flour, baking soda, and salt.</li>
<li>Add milk and dry ingredients to the banana mixture and mix thoroughly.</li>
<li>Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.</li>
<li>Bake for 45 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.</li>
</ol>
<h2>Notes</h2>
<ul>
<li>Four 3×2×5.5-inch pans: 45-minute bake time  </li>
<li>One 9×5×2.5-inch pan: about 1-hour bake time</li>
</ul>
